dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni run out (Gayle) 15 (26b 1x4 0x6) SR: 57.69

dismissalComment.html: Dhoni drives a full one hard towards Gayle who dives and half stops the ball. The batsmen set off for a quick single. Bucknor refers it to the third umpire and after many replays the decision, a close one, is that Dhoni is short of his crease!

commentTextItems.html: FOUR! That's it! Sreesanth goes for the yorker and it's just a touch too full, Sarwan gives himself a bit of room and clobbers the ball through cover for a boundary that seals India's fate!

commentPostTextItems.html: That is a well-deserved win for West Indies and they take a 2-1 lead in this five-match series! Sarwan, with 115 has easily been the star of the day.
The crowd is going crazy celebrating this win, and why not?
At one stage earlier in the day India were coasting at 211 for 3, but from there they lost it, making only 245 in 50 overs.
After that Sarwan, well supported by Shivnarine Chanderpaul, took the game away
This is Anand Vasu, signing off, thanking you for being with Cricinfo for this game.

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels lbw b Sreesanth 11 (32b 1x4 0x6) SR: 34.37

dismissalComment.html: first-blood! good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and coming in with the angle, bit of a skidder - Samuels rocks back in an effort to whip it away through midwicket but fails to make contact and the ball hits him high on the pad, loud appeal and the dreaded finger goes up

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle c Dhoni b Agarkar 40 (65b 5x4 1x6) SR: 61.53

dismissalComment.html: got'm! that's the wicket they wanted! short of a good length delivery, pitched on middle and off and shaping away a touch, Gayle had no option but to play at it and the resultant edge goes straight to Dhoni behind the stumps - Agarkar with the all important breakthrough, West Indies three down.

dismissalText.commentary: Brian Lara c Dravid b Harbhajan Singh 5 (11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: beauty! tossed up on the middle and leg stump line, turning right across, Lara pushes forward - looking to work it away towards midwicket, ball turns across just enough to kiss the outside edge and goes straight to Dravid at first slip who takes it on the second attempt, big wicket and this match is back in the balance

dismissalText.commentary: Shivnarine Chanderpaul lbw b Pathan 58 (68b 4x4 1x6) SR: 85.29

dismissalComment.html: Pathan goes for the yorker, it's a touch too full, Chanderpaul looks to flick, misses and is hit on the pad, loud shout and it's upheld! Chanderpaul is gone for 58 but it might just be a case of too little too late from India. Just 9 runs needed for victory now.

dismissalComment.html: RUN OUT! Can you believe it? A full ball outside the off, driven inside out through cover, Pathan fields on the ropes and throws the ball in. Sarwan calls for the second, then changes his mind and it's a big mix-up! Not over yet apparently ...
